## Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)

### Q1: How do I reset my GitHub password?
- A: Go to the [Password Reset page](https://github.com/password_reset) and enter your email address to receive a reset link.

### Q2: Can I use my personal email for GitHub instead of my GWU email?
- A: Yes, but itâ€™s recommended to use your GWU email for student and university-related projects, especially to apply for GitHub's educational benefits.

### Q3: How do I assign multiple people to an issue?
- A: You can assign multiple people by selecting additional assignees in the **Assignees** section on the right side of the issue page.

### Q4: Can I tag people outside my organization?
- A: Yes, you can tag anyone with a GitHub account by using **@username**, but ensure the person is relevant to the issue.

### Q5: What are **Milestones** used for?
- A: Milestones help track progress by grouping multiple issues. You can use them to track the completion of features or project phases.

### Q6: How do I prioritize issues?
- A: You can prioritize issues by using **Labels** (e.g., **high-priority**, **low-priority**) or by tagging relevant users to ensure faster attention.

